From 93b745bb8d5b520629c0e3a5a728e086ddb9a15d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Coda Agent <coda@local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 16:50:43 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(cli): add --orch flag and window-mode to _coda_attach

Card #95: foundational CLI change for features-as-orchestrator-windows.

- lib/feature.sh: parse --orch <name> / --orch=<name>; pass
  CODA_ORCH_TARGET=${SESSION_PREFIX}orch--<name> and
  CODA_ORCH_WINDOW_MODE=1 through to _coda_attach. Env trigger
  CODA_ORCH_WINDOW_MODE=1 with no resolvable target warns and
  falls back to session-mode (discovery is card #94).
- lib/core.sh: _coda_attach gains a window-mode branch. When the
  target orch session exists, it skips _layout_init and calls
  _layout_spawn with CODA_LAYOUT_TARGET=<session>:<window>. Window
  name is derived by stripping SESSION_PREFIX and <project>-- from
  the feature session name. When in TMUX, switches via
  switch-client; else plain tmux attach to orch session. Falls back
  to session-mode with a warning when target is missing.
- layouts/default.sh, layouts/classic.sh: _layout_spawn honors
  CODA_LAYOUT_TARGET env var so window-mode can specify
  session:window target.
- Tests: new bats tests cover --orch parsing (both forms), env-only
  trigger, window-mode path when orch exists / is missing, and
  _layout_spawn target handling. Existing tests/window-mode.sh
  integration harness still passes.

Off by default. Behavior is byte-identical when --orch unset and
CODA_ORCH_WINDOW_MODE is unset.
